-- Shell Restarting Unit at Scotford Refinery in Alberta
-- B y   M a r k   C h e d i a k
-- 2012-04-22T15:41:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-22/shell-restarting-unit-at-scotford-refinery-in-alberta.html
Royal Dutch Shell Plc is restarting
a unit at the Scotford refinery in  Alberta .  The company began restart at 2 p.m. local time yesterday,
according to a message left on a community information line.
Flaring associated with the work will continue for about 24
hours.  The Scotford complex, 40 kilometers (25 miles) northeast of
Edmonton, includes an oil-sands upgrader and a refinery. The
refinery can process about 98,000 barrels a day, according to
data compiled by Bloomberg.  Editor: Greg Storey  To contact the reporter on this story:
